episodes.title: Pilot
episodes.plot: Agent Dana Scully is instructed to debunk an FBI project dubbed "The X-Files," paranormal cases that have been reopened by Agent Fox Mulder.

episodes.title: Deep Throat
episodes.plot: Mulder and Scully investigate the mysterious case of a military test pilot who disappeared after experiencing strange psychotic behaviour.

episodes.title: Squeeze
episodes.plot: Mulder and Scully search for a humanoid killer whose savage murder spree reoccurs every 30 years.

episodes.title: Conduit
episodes.plot: Mulder becomes obsessed with solving a case that closely parallels an "encounter" he experienced as a child.

episodes.title: The Jersey Devil
episodes.plot: Mulder and Scully track a legendary creature that has roamed the New Jersey countryside for over 40 years.

episodes.title: Shadows
episodes.plot: Mulder and Scully investigate the deaths of two men believed to have been killed by a powerful psychokinetic force.

episodes.title: Ghost in the Machine
episodes.plot: On Halloween, Mulder and Scully investigate the death of a corporate executive who may have been murdered by a thinking computer.

episodes.title: Ice
episodes.plot: Mulder and Scully are sent to investigate when a team of geophysicists stationed at a remote Alaskan outpost are killed by a parasitic alien life form.

episodes.title: Space
episodes.plot: When a space shuttle mission is sabotaged, Mulder suspects it may be the work of an alien spirit that inhabits the body of a former Gemini astronaut.

episodes.title: Fallen Angel
episodes.plot: The future of the X-Files project is jeopardized after Mulder secretly infiltrates the government cover-up of a UFO crash.

episodes.title: Eve
episodes.plot: Mulder and Scully search for two missing girls who disappeared after their fathers were murdered in an identical fashion.

episodes.title: Fire
episodes.plot: Mulder and Scully join forces with an inspector from Scotland Yard when a man with pyrokinetic powers stalks members of the British aristocracy.

episodes.title: Beyond the Sea
episodes.plot: Scully believes that the psychic predictions of a death row inmate are the only hope in the kidnapping of two college students.

episodes.title: Gender Bender
episodes.plot: A religious sect becomes the prime suspect in a murder spree.

episodes.title: Lazarus
episodes.plot: The consciousness of a dangerous criminal possesses an FBI agent who is also Scully's ex-boyfriend.

episodes.title: Young at Heart
episodes.plot: A criminal believed to have died in a prison years earlier wages a vendetta against Mulder.

episodes.title: E.B.E.
episodes.plot: Mulder and Scully become the focus of a disinformation campaign when they attempt to trace the government's secret transport of an alien life form.

episodes.title: Miracle Man
episodes.plot: The agents investigate a ministry led by a man whose son possesses the power to heal, and to kill, with a touch of his hand.

episodes.title: Shapes
episodes.plot: A creature, possibly from Native American lore, is suspected of killing a man, bringing Mulder and Scully to the Indian reservation where the attack occurred in order to uncover its identity.

episodes.title: Darkness Falls
episodes.plot: A group of loggers working in a remote forest unearths thousands of deadly insectlike creatures that paralyze and cocoon their victims. Scully, Mulder and a few others end up trapped there.

episodes.title: Tooms
episodes.plot: Eugene Tooms, a supernatural killer whom Mulder helped incarcerate, is released on parole.

episodes.title: Born Again
episodes.plot: An 8-year-old girl is the prime suspect in a series of bizarre, seemingly unrelated deaths.

episodes.title: Roland
episodes.plot: When scientists at an aeronautics lab die under mysterious circumstances, the agents suspect a mentally challenged janitor may be the culprit.

episodes.title: The Erlenmeyer Flask
episodes.plot: Deep Throat tips Mulder to a critically important case involving a missing fugitive and the cloning of extraterrestrial viruses.
